REFERENTIAL-SEM.name: REFERENTIAL-SEM
REFERENTIAL-SEM.comment: The root type for all things that can be referred to: abstract meaning for THIS and IT

PHYS-OBJECT.name: PHYS-OBJECT
PHYS-OBJECT.comment: All physical objects: things that have substance

SITUATION-ROOT.name: SITUATION-ROOT
SITUATION-ROOT.comment: root for all events, whether verbal or nominal

EVENT-OF-CHANGE.name: EVENT-OF-CHANGE
EVENT-OF-CHANGE.comment: Events that involve change or force: should ahve an AGENT or AFFECTED role

OCCURRING.name: OCCURRING
OCCURRING.comment: event occurrence - e.g., an explosion happened

EVENT-OF-ACTION.name: EVENT-OF-ACTION
EVENT-OF-ACTION.comment: events that involve :agent (whether intentional or not)

EVENT-OF-AWARENESS.name: EVENT-OF-AWARENESS
EVENT-OF-AWARENESS.comment: Events involving changing or mental state or awareness

EVENT-OF-UNDERGOING-ACTION.name: EVENT-OF-UNDERGOING-ACTION
EVENT-OF-UNDERGOING-ACTION.comment: A small class of events that take an affected but do not allow an AGENT construction (though might be caused as in he died from the plague

EVENT-OF-CAUSATION.name: EVENT-OF-CAUSATION
EVENT-OF-CAUSATION.comment: events involving an AGENT acting on an AFFECTED

EVENT-OF-CREATION.name: EVENT-OF-CREATION
EVENT-OF-CREATION.comment: Events that involve creating some new object (typically the AFFECTED-RESULT)

EVENT-OF-STATE.name: EVENT-OF-STATE
EVENT-OF-STATE.comment: Events describing a state of affairs holding

EVENT-OF-EXPERIENCE.name: EVENT-OF-EXPERIENCE
EVENT-OF-EXPERIENCE.comment: A stative event involving a sentient being in a mental state

EVENT-TYPE.name: EVENT-TYPE
EVENT-TYPE.comment:
classification of situated events based on social or other criteria, and typically realized by nominals, i.e.,
        they are not nominalization of verbal events

ABSTRACT-OBJECT.name: ABSTRACT-OBJECT
ABSTRACT-OBJECT.comment: abstract objects, mental constructions, with no physical realization

ABSTRACT-OBJECT-NONTEMPORAL.name: ABSTRACT-OBJECT-NONTEMPORAL
ABSTRACT-OBJECT-NONTEMPORAL.comment: formal constructions with no temporal existence: e.g., facts, types, ...

TANGIBLE-ABSTRACT-OBJECT.name: TANGIBLE-ABSTRACT-OBJECT
TANGIBLE-ABSTRACT-OBJECT.comment: abstract notions that act like things. They can be created, transfered, e.g., mental objects

UNIT.name: UNIT
UNIT.comment: names of units in various scales/domains

MENTAL-CONSTRUCTION.name: MENTAL-CONSTRUCTION
MENTAL-CONSTRUCTION.comment: constructions of the mind: plans, goals, beliefs, ...

DOMAIN-PROPERTY.name: DOMAIN-PROPERTY
DOMAIN-PROPERTY.comment: these are modifiers that characterize an object/event with respect to a scale/domain (in ONT::DOMAIN)

PART.name: PART
PART.comment: Part is actually a conceptualization of things that fill the part-of role

PREDICATE.name: PREDICATE
PREDICATE.comment: predications that require a subcat to form a modifier, typically adverbials (e.g., on, as well as)

LEAST-EXTENT.name: LEAST-EXTENT
LEAST-EXTENT.comment: to the least extent, to any extent

SEQUENCE-POSITION.name: SEQUENCE-POSITION
SEQUENCE-POSITION.comment: Position related to discourse. e.g., First, we laugh

POSITION-RELN.name: POSITION-RELN
POSITION-RELN.comment: Spatial relations that locate one object (the figure) in terms of another object (the ground), which often is implicit

AT-SCALE-VALUE.name: AT-SCALE-VALUE
AT-SCALE-VALUE.comment: The main predicate for associating an object with a value on a scale

POSITION-AS-POINT-RELN.name: POSITION-AS-POINT-RELN
POSITION-AS-POINT-RELN.comment: locating an object (FIGURE) wrt a point-like object (GROUND)

AT-LOC.name: AT-LOC
AT-LOC.comment: prototypical locating of a FIGURE wrt a point-like GROUND

POS-WRT-CONTAINMENT-RELN.name: POS-WRT-CONTAINMENT-RELN
POS-WRT-CONTAINMENT-RELN.comment: locating an object (typically rthe FIGURE) within an extended object (typically the GROUND)

IN-LOC.name: IN-LOC
IN-LOC.comment: FIGURE is within or inside the GROUND

CONTAIN-RELN.name: CONTAIN-RELN
CONTAIN-RELN.comment: a kind of Inverse of IN-LOC, but can't be used as a result location

DELIMIT-RELN.name: DELIMIT-RELN
DELIMIT-RELN.comment: the FIGURE has a value in a rnage that is delimited by the GROUND, e.g., within five dollars of the estimate, within five miles of starbucks

COMPLEX-GROUND-RELN.name: COMPLEX-GROUND-RELN
COMPLEX-GROUND-RELN.comment: FIGURE is located wrt a set of objects that comprise the GROUND. e.g., between X and Y, among the participants

ORIENTED-LOC-RELN.name: ORIENTED-LOC-RELN
ORIENTED-LOC-RELN.comment: FIGURE is located by a directional relationship with the GROUND

DIRECTIONAL-VERT.name: DIRECTIONAL-VERT
DIRECTIONAL-VERT.comment: FIGURE is related via a vertical orientation to the GROUND

BELOW.name: BELOW
BELOW.comment: FIGURE is lower on some vertical scale than the GROUND

DOWN.name: DOWN
DOWN.comment: FIGURE is lower on a scale

ABOVE.name: ABOVE
ABOVE.comment: FIGURE is higher on some vertical scale than the GROUND

UP.name: UP
UP.comment: FIGURE is higher on some vertical scale than the GROUND

ORIENTS-TO.name: ORIENTS-TO
ORIENTS-TO.comment: FIGURE is located by an object defined by an orientation wrt an object. e.g., to the east, to the back

NAVIGATIONAL-RELN.name: NAVIGATIONAL-RELN
NAVIGATIONAL-RELN.comment: Figure is related by a cardinal directional reln to ground

POSITION-WRT-AREA-RELN.name: POSITION-WRT-AREA-RELN
POSITION-WRT-AREA-RELN.comment: Position of FIGURE defined in terms or a relationship to an area (the GROUND)

DISTRIBUTED-POS.name: DISTRIBUTED-POS
DISTRIBUTED-POS.comment: FIGURE is distributed over the GROUND

ACROSS.name: ACROSS
ACROSS.comment: FIGURE is a slice through the GROUND from one side to the other. Conceptually on the GROUND

POS-AS-OPPOSITE.name: POS-AS-OPPOSITE
POS-AS-OPPOSITE.comment: FIGURE is on an opposite side of an area wrt some reference object: e.g., it is across the street

AROUND.name: AROUND
AROUND.comment: FIGURE is an area surrounding the boundary of the GROUND, or distrubuted over the GROUND

THROUGH.name: THROUGH
THROUGH.comment: FIGURE crosses the GROUND, conceptually IN the ground

POSITION-WRT-LINEAR-AREA-RELN.name: POSITION-WRT-LINEAR-AREA-RELN
POSITION-WRT-LINEAR-AREA-RELN.comment: FIGURE is defined wrt an area (the GROUND) that has a linear orientation

POS-EXTENDED-ALONG-LINEAR-AREA.name: POS-EXTENDED-ALONG-LINEAR-AREA
POS-EXTENDED-ALONG-LINEAR-AREA.comment: FIGURE is located within the linear area (GROUND). e.g., I found it along the street. We walked along the street

POS-RELATIVE-WRT-TRAJECTORY.name: POS-RELATIVE-WRT-TRAJECTORY
POS-RELATIVE-WRT-TRAJECTORY.comment: FIGURE is located along a linear area wrt some other object (GROUND)

POS-BEFORE-IN-TRAJECTORY.name: POS-BEFORE-IN-TRAJECTORY
POS-BEFORE-IN-TRAJECTORY.comment: FIGURE is before the GROUND wrt a linear area

POS-AFTER-IN-TRAJECTORY.name: POS-AFTER-IN-TRAJECTORY
POS-AFTER-IN-TRAJECTORY.comment: FIGURE is after the GROUND wrt a linear area

TO-LOC.name: TO-LOC
TO-LOC.comment: the generic goal role: might be a physical object (as possessor) or a resulting state

DIRECTION.name: DIRECTION
DIRECTION.comment: a direction = a spatial relation between the location (FIGURE) of an object and its previous location

DIRECTION-WRT-ENTITY.name: DIRECTION-WRT-ENTITY
DIRECTION-WRT-ENTITY.comment: direction wrt respect to a given entity (the GROUND), i.e., the relation between the FIGUREs orginal and final position is defined with respect to the GROUND

DIRECTION-FORWARD.name: DIRECTION-FORWARD
DIRECTION-FORWARD.comment: FIGURE moves forward from its original position, where forward is defined by the orientation of the GROUND

DIRECTION-BACKWARD.name: DIRECTION-BACKWARD
DIRECTION-BACKWARD.comment: FIGURE moves backward from its original position, where backward is defined by the orientation of the GROUND

DIRECTION-RIGHTWARD.name: DIRECTION-RIGHTWARD
DIRECTION-RIGHTWARD.comment: direction rightward wrt respect to a given entity (the GROUND)

DIRECTION-LEFTWARD.name: DIRECTION-LEFTWARD
DIRECTION-LEFTWARD.comment: direction leftward wrt respect to a given entity (the GROUND)

TOWARDS.name: TOWARDS
TOWARDS.comment: direction towards from a given entity (the GROUND)

AWAY.name: AWAY
AWAY.comment: direction away a given entity (the GROUND)

DIRECTION-WRT-VERTICALITY.name: DIRECTION-WRT-VERTICALITY
DIRECTION-WRT-VERTICALITY.comment: direction wrt respect to verticality (e.g., gravity or a 'vertical' scale, e.g., temperature), possibly also related to a extended object, e.g., a street, a body, which is the GROUND

DIRECTION-DOWN.name: DIRECTION-DOWN
DIRECTION-DOWN.comment: This is the particle 'down' and is relative to some scale/domain: e.g., the temperature is down, move the ball down

DIRECTION-DOWN-GROUND.name: DIRECTION-DOWN-GROUND
DIRECTION-DOWN-GROUND.comment: this is the transitive 'down' that has a GROUND that describes a physical object and locations objects or events

DIRECTION-UP.name: DIRECTION-UP
DIRECTION-UP.comment: This is the particle 'up' and is relative to some scale/domain: e.g., the temperature is up, move the ball up

DIRECTION-UP-GROUND.name: DIRECTION-UP-GROUND
DIRECTION-UP-GROUND.comment: this is the transitive 'up' that has a GROUND that describes a physical object and locations objects or events

DIRECTION-WRT-CONTAINMENT.name: DIRECTION-WRT-CONTAINMENT
DIRECTION-WRT-CONTAINMENT.comment: direction relative to containment in some object (the GROUND)

DIRECTION-IN.name: DIRECTION-IN
DIRECTION-IN.comment: direction involving moving into some object (the GROUND)

DIRECTION-OUT.name: DIRECTION-OUT
DIRECTION-OUT.comment: direction involving moving into some object (the GROUND)

IMPLICIT-OVERLAP.name: IMPLICIT-OVERLAP
IMPLICIT-OVERLAP.comment: this is the implicit relation between the events in sentences like He walked down the street whistling a tune

TIME-OBJECT.name: TIME-OBJECT
TIME-OBJECT.comment: objects that refer to temporal locations in some way

PHASE.name: PHASE
PHASE.comment: e.g., phases of the moon, stage of the project. This type represents stages of a sequence that is more abstract than time.

RECURRING-TIME-OF-DAY.name: RECURRING-TIME-OF-DAY
RECURRING-TIME-OF-DAY.comment: recurring moments of the day, defined by some event

MONTH.name: MONTH
MONTH.comment: time interval of a named month

DATE-OBJECT.name: DATE-OBJECT
DATE-OBJECT.comment: classification of time intervals with respect to some conceptual organization (e.g., calendar)

DATE-OBJECT-ON.name: DATE-OBJECT-ON
DATE-OBJECT-ON.comment: date objects that use ON - e.g., on Monday, on my birthday

DATE-OBJECT-IN.name: DATE-OBJECT-IN
DATE-OBJECT-IN.comment: temporal objects that use IN - e.g., in June

RECURRING-EVENT.name: RECURRING-EVENT
RECURRING-EVENT.comment: events that recur every year (or some time interval)

HOLIDAY.name: HOLIDAY
HOLIDAY.comment: recurring events based on religious or social activities

DAY-STAGE.name: DAY-STAGE
DAY-STAGE.comment: a regular part of the day

PROFESSIONAL.name: PROFESSIONAL
PROFESSIONAL.comment: a person defined by a role that they play. e.g., doctor, leader, ...

STRUCTURE-EXTERNAL-COMPONENT.name: STRUCTURE-EXTERNAL-COMPONENT
STRUCTURE-EXTERNAL-COMPONENT.comment: parts of exterior of buildings: e.g., roof, window

FURNISHINGS-COMPONENT.name: FURNISHINGS-COMPONENT
FURNISHINGS-COMPONENT.comment: parts typically of furnishings: e.g., drawer

BEDDING.name: BEDDING
BEDDING.comment: objects related to bedding: pillow, blanket

LOC-DEF-BY-GOAL.name: LOC-DEF-BY-GOAL
LOC-DEF-BY-GOAL.comment: place related to a trajectory by a goal: destination

LOC-DEF-BY-INTERSECTION.name: LOC-DEF-BY-INTERSECTION
LOC-DEF-BY-INTERSECTION.comment: place defined by the intersection of two lines/areas

AREA-DEF-BY-USE.name: AREA-DEF-BY-USE
AREA-DEF-BY-USE.comment: places defined by their function: e.g.,  lot, plot, region, scene, section, site, territory, zone

LOC-DEFINED-BY-CONTRAST.name: LOC-DEFINED-BY-CONTRAST
LOC-DEFINED-BY-CONTRAST.comment: Objects that are subparts of larger surface but delineated by a contrasting property: e.g., spot, patch

OBJECT-DEPENDENT-LOCATION.name: OBJECT-DEPENDENT-LOCATION
OBJECT-DEPENDENT-LOCATION.comment: these are locations defined relative to another object

FOOD-GRAINS.name: FOOD-GRAINS
FOOD-GRAINS.comment: grains and grain products for food

SYSTEM.name: SYSTEM
SYSTEM.comment: An interconnected group of objects, abstract or physical

ECOSYSTEM.name: ECOSYSTEM
ECOSYSTEM.comment: An interconnected group of] entities fo5ming an ecosystem

STRUCTURE.name: STRUCTURE
STRUCTURE.comment: A collection of objects organized for some purpose

ECONOMIC-SYSTEM.name: ECONOMIC-SYSTEM
ECONOMIC-SYSTEM.comment: An interconnected group of entities forming an economy

ACTING.name: ACTING
ACTING.comment: abstract event of doing something: behave, activity, ...

CAUSE-EFFECT.name: CAUSE-EFFECT
CAUSE-EFFECT.comment: an AGENT causes some event to occur or proposition to become true. Usually the verbs that fall under this category are very general causal verbs that take other events as their arguments and are positive causes- i.e., events are caused to happen as opposed to negative causes as in an event is prevented.

INHIBIT-EFFECT.name: INHIBIT-EFFECT
INHIBIT-EFFECT.comment: an AGENT prevents some activity from occuring or proposition from becoming true

HAVE-INFLUENCE.name: HAVE-INFLUENCE
HAVE-INFLUENCE.comment: an AGENT causes some interaction with another agent

CAUSE-INTERACT.name: CAUSE-INTERACT
CAUSE-INTERACT.comment: an AGENT causes some interaction with another agent

AGENT-INTERACTION.name: AGENT-INTERACTION
AGENT-INTERACTION.comment: events that involve the interaction of two or more agents

COMMUNICATION.name: COMMUNICATION
COMMUNICATION.comment: activity that involves transfer of information between agents

LOCUTION.name: LOCUTION
LOCUTION.comment: activities that solely address the mechanics of communicating: e.g., pronounce

ILLOCUTION.name: ILLOCUTION
ILLOCUTION.comment: activities describe the act performed in saying something (cf. Austin)

REPRESENTATIVE.name: REPRESENTATIVE
REPRESENTATIVE.comment: speech act that expresses the speakers belief about what is true (cf. Searle)

LOADED-CLAIM.name: LOADED-CLAIM
LOADED-CLAIM.comment: speech act that expresses the speakers belief with a particular purpose (e.g., accuse, complain)

COMMISSIVE.name: COMMISSIVE
COMMISSIVE.comment: speech act that expresses the speakers commitment to future acts (cf. Searle)

DIRECTIVE.name: DIRECTIVE
DIRECTIVE.comment: speech act that ia aimed at influences the hearer's future actions (cf. Searle)

CONVENTIONAL-SPEECH-ACT.name: CONVENTIONAL-SPEECH-ACT
CONVENTIONAL-SPEECH-ACT.comment: speech act that is conventional in nature and generally determined by an explicit performative verb (cf. Searle)

EXCLAMATION.name: EXCLAMATION
EXCLAMATION.comment: communicative act that expresses an emotional response with no propositional content

PERLOCUTION.name: PERLOCUTION
PERLOCUTION.comment: activities describe the act performed by saying something but beyond the speaker's control (cf. Austin)

MOTION.name: MOTION
MOTION.comment: events of motion through some space (physical or abstract). Even though many motion verbs express simply undergoing motion, all these verbs allow to possibiliity of an AGENT

AWARENESS.name: AWARENESS
AWARENESS.comment: a state in which an EXPERIENCER holds some attitude towards a proposition

ATTITUDE-OF-BELIEF.name: ATTITUDE-OF-BELIEF
ATTITUDE-OF-BELIEF.comment: a state that captures an EXPERIENCER to some degree of belief or disbelief

PERCEPTION.name: PERCEPTION
PERCEPTION.comment: an EXPERIENCER is perceiving something (remember its stative)

OBJECTIVE-INFLUENCE.name: OBJECTIVE-INFLUENCE
OBJECTIVE-INFLUENCE.comment: an AGENT influences the AFFECTED role in some way (typically unspecified by the verb)

BODY-MANIPULATION.name: BODY-MANIPULATION
BODY-MANIPULATION.comment: and AGENT grasps something to manipulate it

EXPECTATION.name: EXPECTATION
EXPECTATION.comment: EXPERIENCER expects some proposition to hold

DIRECTED-COMMUNICATION.name: DIRECTED-COMMUNICATION
DIRECTED-COMMUNICATION.comment: typically asymmetric extended interaction controlled by a single agent

RESPONSE.name: RESPONSE
RESPONSE.comment: Communicative act that is in direct response to a previous communicative act

INTENTION.name: INTENTION
INTENTION.comment: EXPERIENCERS has intention to achieve some situation (e.g., aim, intend, mean)

CONTROL-MANAGE.name: CONTROL-MANAGE
CONTROL-MANAGE.comment: an agent controls another object, typically by some manipulation (physical, adding a substance,...)

GROUPING.name: GROUPING
GROUPING.comment: a  classification, category, variety of things. Not a set of objects!

SYSTEM-ABSTR.name: SYSTEM-ABSTR
SYSTEM-ABSTR.comment: An interconnected group of objects, abstract or physical

NUMBER-UNIT.name: NUMBER-UNIT
NUMBER-UNIT.comment: words that name measurement units in scales: foot, mile, ...

LEVEL.name: LEVEL
LEVEL.comment: words that act as predicates that return the value on a scale/domain: What is the X on this scale?  Note: We exclude words that are identical to the names of the scales they pertain to (e.g., What is the height on the height scale?)

LOCATED-EVENT.name: LOCATED-EVENT
LOCATED-EVENT.comment: events that are located in time/space - e.g., riot, war, ...

REQUIREMENTS.name: REQUIREMENTS
REQUIREMENTS.comment: reference or rules that must be met to satisfy evaluation

STANDARD.name: STANDARD
STANDARD.comment: the ideal in terms of which something can be judged

EVALUATION-ATTRIBUTE-VAL.name: EVALUATION-ATTRIBUTE-VAL
EVALUATION-ATTRIBUTE-VAL.comment: properties which need an observer to be recognized -- subjective to the observer

FRESHNESS-VAL.name: FRESHNESS-VAL
FRESHNESS-VAL.comment: relating to how recently an object was made or obtained

COST-VAL.name: COST-VAL
COST-VAL.comment: properties having to do with evaluation of cost

ACCEPTABILITY-VAL.name: ACCEPTABILITY-VAL
ACCEPTABILITY-VAL.comment: properties having to do with good vs. bad

ABILITY-VAL.name: ABILITY-VAL
ABILITY-VAL.comment: evaluation of ability or capability to do something

HARMFULNESS-VAL.name: HARMFULNESS-VAL
HARMFULNESS-VAL.comment: regarding capability of harm or injury (compare to ont::safety-val)

SAFETY-VAL.name: SAFETY-VAL
SAFETY-VAL.comment: regarding liability or exposure to danger, risk or peril (compare to ont::harmfulness-val)

IMPORTANCE-VAL.name: IMPORTANCE-VAL
IMPORTANCE-VAL.comment: of primary (i.e., major, significant), secondary (i.e., minor), or no importance

TYPICALITY-VAL.name: TYPICALITY-VAL
TYPICALITY-VAL.comment: abiding by or breaking with customary or usual practices

FUNDAMENTAL-VAL.name: FUNDAMENTAL-VAL
FUNDAMENTAL-VAL.comment: forming a necessary base or core

WORTHINESS-VAL.name: WORTHINESS-VAL
WORTHINESS-VAL.comment: evaluation attributes dealing with the value or worth of something

PLAINNESS-VAL.name: PLAINNESS-VAL
PLAINNESS-VAL.comment: evaluation attributes dealing with plainess or elaborateness of something

MERE-VAL.name: MERE-VAL
MERE-VAL.comment: being nothing other than what's specified

ACTUALITY-VAL.name: ACTUALITY-VAL
ACTUALITY-VAL.comment: existing or occuring in fact vs. imagined or supposed

AUTHENTICITY-VAL.name: AUTHENTICITY-VAL
AUTHENTICITY-VAL.comment: truly what it is said to be vs. made as imitation

INFORMATION-PROPERTY-VAL.name: INFORMATION-PROPERTY-VAL
INFORMATION-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties regarding the evaluation of information, knowledge, or understanding (e.g. credible, correct, consistent)

CONSISTENT-VAL.name: CONSISTENT-VAL
CONSISTENT-VAL.comment: marked by a (il)logical or (dis)orderly consistent relation of parts

CORRECTNESS-VAL.name: CORRECTNESS-VAL
CORRECTNESS-VAL.comment: describing the quality of being error-free or error-prone

PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-VAL.name: PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-VAL
PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties pertaining to the attributes of physical entities or substances. note many physical adjectives can be used on non-physical objects

CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-VAL.name: CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-VAL
CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties regarding the configuration, arrangement, or layout of elements

CONSTRICTING-VAL.name: CONSTRICTING-VAL
CONSTRICTING-VAL.comment: describes how constricting something is with regards to another item (close-fitting vs. loose-fitting)

BINDING-VAL.name: BINDING-VAL
BINDING-VAL.comment: describes how firmly something is fixed in place

FLOW-VAL.name: FLOW-VAL
FLOW-VAL.comment: presence or absense of obstruction, e.g., for routes

SUBSTANTIAL-PROPERTY-VAL.name: SUBSTANTIAL-PROPERTY-VAL
SUBSTANTIAL-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties having to do with characteristic substance of the described object

MEDIUM.name: MEDIUM
MEDIUM.comment: means of production and dissemination (c.f. ont::mode)

SENSORY-PROPERTY-VAL.name: SENSORY-PROPERTY-VAL
SENSORY-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties that have to do with sensory input

PART-WHOLE-VAL.name: PART-WHOLE-VAL
PART-WHOLE-VAL.comment: properties describing the relationship between the complete or complex whole and its parts

COMPLETENESS-VAL.name: COMPLETENESS-VAL
COMPLETENESS-VAL.comment: having or not having all the necessary parts

REMAINING-VAL.name: REMAINING-VAL
REMAINING-VAL.comment: remaining after reaching a complete whole

SUPPLEMENTAL-VAL.name: SUPPLEMENTAL-VAL
SUPPLEMENTAL-VAL.comment: supplemental addition to a complete whole

BODY-RELATED-PROPERTY-VAL.name: BODY-RELATED-PROPERTY-VAL
BODY-RELATED-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties having to do with human/animal body

BODY-PROPERTY-VAL.name: BODY-PROPERTY-VAL
BODY-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties having to do with human/animal body conditions or states

PROCESS-STATUS-VAL.name: PROCESS-STATUS-VAL
PROCESS-STATUS-VAL.comment: properties relating to status of processes

EFFECTIVENESS-VAL.name: EFFECTIVENESS-VAL
EFFECTIVENESS-VAL.comment: evaluation attributes dealing with the effectiveness or efficacy of something

ANIMAL-PROPENSITY-VAL.name: ANIMAL-PROPENSITY-VAL
ANIMAL-PROPENSITY-VAL.comment: properties relating to human or animal tendencies or inclinations to behave in a particular manner

SOCIAL-INTERACTION-VAL.name: SOCIAL-INTERACTION-VAL
SOCIAL-INTERACTION-VAL.comment: properties of human behavior having to do with social interaction, e.g. friendly, kind, mean

DIMENSIONAL-PROPERTY-VAL.name: DIMENSIONAL-PROPERTY-VAL
DIMENSIONAL-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties pertaining to dimensions and measurable extents

POSITION-ON-DIMENSION-SCALE-VAL.name: POSITION-ON-DIMENSION-SCALE-VAL
POSITION-ON-DIMENSION-SCALE-VAL.comment: indicates a position given a dimensional scale. These adjectives do not specify the shape, direction, or alignment of the scale.

SIZE-VAL.name: SIZE-VAL
SIZE-VAL.comment: indicates relative extent or magnitude of something on a size scale

NON-VERTICAL-VAL.name: NON-VERTICAL-VAL
NON-VERTICAL-VAL.comment: size specific to non-vertical linear scale

VERTICAL-VAL.name: VERTICAL-VAL
VERTICAL-VAL.comment: size specific to vertical linear scale

SHORT-VAL.name: SHORT-VAL
SHORT-VAL.comment: less in orientation on a linear scale -- does not indicate horizontality or verticality of the object

LONG.name: LONG
LONG.comment: more in orientation on a linear scale -- does not indicate horizontality or verticality of the object

RELATIVE-TO-HEIGHT-VAL.name: RELATIVE-TO-HEIGHT-VAL
RELATIVE-TO-HEIGHT-VAL.comment: size specification relative to height. E.g. fat means more in  horizontal orientation with respect to the height

FAT-VAL.name: FAT-VAL
FAT-VAL.comment: more in  horizontal orientation with respect to the height

SKINNY-VAL.name: SKINNY-VAL
SKINNY-VAL.comment: less in horizontal orientation with respect to the height

LARGE.name: LARGE
LARGE.comment: more in orientation on a size scale

SMALL.name: SMALL
SMALL.comment: negative orientation on a size scale

WEIGHT-VAL.name: WEIGHT-VAL
WEIGHT-VAL.comment: indicates relative extent or magnitude of something on a weight scale

HEAVY.name: HEAVY
HEAVY.comment: indicates more in orientation on a weight scale

LIGHTWEIGHT.name: LIGHTWEIGHT
LIGHTWEIGHT.comment: indicates less in orientation on a weight scale

INTENSITY-VAL.name: INTENSITY-VAL
INTENSITY-VAL.comment: indicates relative extent or magnitude of something on an intensity scale

SEVERITY-VAL.name: SEVERITY-VAL
SEVERITY-VAL.comment: indicates relative extent or magnitude of something on a severity scale

PROPORTION-VAL.name: PROPORTION-VAL
PROPORTION-VAL.comment: indicates relative proportion/ratio on a specified scale

FATTINESS-VAL.name: FATTINESS-VAL
FATTINESS-VAL.comment: indicates relative proportion/ratio on a fattiness scale

PREDEFINED-MEASURE-VAL.name: PREDEFINED-MEASURE-VAL
PREDEFINED-MEASURE-VAL.comment: standardized size/quantity given a predefined measure

ROBUSTNESS-VAL.name: ROBUSTNESS-VAL
ROBUSTNESS-VAL.comment: indicates relative extent on a robustness scale

RELATIONAL-ATTRIBUTE-VAL.name: RELATIONAL-ATTRIBUTE-VAL
RELATIONAL-ATTRIBUTE-VAL.comment: properties that describe an entity with respect to another related entity, an implicit second entity always present when these properties are evoked

ORDERED-VAL.name: ORDERED-VAL
ORDERED-VAL.comment: properties that deal with ordered nature of objects

SEQUENCE-VAL.name: SEQUENCE-VAL
SEQUENCE-VAL.comment: properties that deal with an object's location with respect to another object in an ordered sequence

AGE-VAL.name: AGE-VAL
AGE-VAL.comment: age given the length or duration of existence

HISTORICAL-ERA-VAL.name: HISTORICAL-ERA-VAL
HISTORICAL-ERA-VAL.comment: relating to the distinct periods in history

OBJECT-AFFORDANCES-VAL.name: OBJECT-AFFORDANCES-VAL
OBJECT-AFFORDANCES-VAL.comment: properties pertaining to the function of an entity or an object

FUNCTIONALITY-VAL.name: FUNCTIONALITY-VAL
FUNCTIONALITY-VAL.comment: properties relating to  whether something is functioning as intended

DEFECTIVE-VAL.name: DEFECTIVE-VAL
DEFECTIVE-VAL.comment: not functioning as intended but not broken permanently e.g., printer is printing only in red

NOT-IN-WORKING-ORDER-VAL.name: NOT-IN-WORKING-ORDER-VAL
NOT-IN-WORKING-ORDER-VAL.comment: broken/not-operational more permanently - needs fixing, not switching on

ACTIVITY-VAL.name: ACTIVITY-VAL
ACTIVITY-VAL.comment: properties relating to whether something is operating/active as intended

ACTIVE-OPEN.name: ACTIVE-OPEN
ACTIVE-OPEN.comment: operating as intended, typically a physcal location with operating hours

ACTIVE-ON.name: ACTIVE-ON
ACTIVE-ON.comment: operating as intended, typically due to some switching on/off

INACTIVE.name: INACTIVE
INACTIVE.comment: not operating as intended wrt some process (switch is off)

INACTIVE-OFF.name: INACTIVE-OFF
INACTIVE-OFF.comment: not operating as intended, typically due to some switching on/off

INACTIVE-CLOSED.name: INACTIVE-CLOSED
INACTIVE-CLOSED.comment: not operating as intended,  typically a physcal location with operating hours

STATUS-VAL.name: STATUS-VAL
STATUS-VAL.comment: properties that describe social, political or official status or position

CLASSIFICATION-VAL.name: CLASSIFICATION-VAL
CLASSIFICATION-VAL.comment: official designation that allows access to only authorized persons

COUNTRY-RELATED-VAL.name: COUNTRY-RELATED-VAL
COUNTRY-RELATED-VAL.comment: adjectives relating to a nation or a country

NATIONAL-VAL.name: NATIONAL-VAL
NATIONAL-VAL.comment: having to do with a nation (or its government)

NATIONAL-IDENTITY-VAL.name: NATIONAL-IDENTITY-VAL
NATIONAL-IDENTITY-VAL.comment: identity based on the country/region of origin or residence

CITY-RELATED-VAL.name: CITY-RELATED-VAL
CITY-RELATED-VAL.comment: having to do with a city (or its government)

PSYCHOLOGICAL-PROPERTY-VAL.name: PSYCHOLOGICAL-PROPERTY-VAL
PSYCHOLOGICAL-PROPERTY-VAL.comment: properties pertaining to psychological, mental or emotional states

SENSIBILITY-VAL.name: SENSIBILITY-VAL
SENSIBILITY-VAL.comment: describing mental ability or sensitivity to respond to emotional influences

ATTENTION-VAL.name: ATTENTION-VAL
ATTENTION-VAL.comment: attributes that indicate the presence or absence of attention

EVOKING-EMOTION-VAL.name: EVOKING-EMOTION-VAL
EVOKING-EMOTION-VAL.comment: attributes that indicate the evocation of a particular emotion

EMOTIONAL-VAL.name: EMOTIONAL-VAL
EMOTIONAL-VAL.comment: state of having a particular emotion

RESULTING-STATE-VAL.name: RESULTING-STATE-VAL
RESULTING-STATE-VAL.comment: adjectives that describe the resulting states of the verb that it pertains to

ASSOCIATED-WITH-VAL.name: ASSOCIATED-WITH-VAL
ASSOCIATED-WITH-VAL.comment: adjectives that classify the noun that it is pertaining to

BODY-SYSTEM-VAL.name: BODY-SYSTEM-VAL
BODY-SYSTEM-VAL.comment: adjective having to do with body systems

BODY-PART-VAL.name: BODY-PART-VAL
BODY-PART-VAL.comment: adjectives having to do with body parts

NORTH.name: NORTH
NORTH.comment: modifiers that select a subarea of a larger area: e.g., northern Canada

DOMAIN.name: DOMAIN
DOMAIN.comment: Nouns that name domain/scales, and can serve as relational nouns (e.g., the COLOR of the box)

ATTRIBUTIVE-SCALE.name: ATTRIBUTIVE-SCALE
ATTRIBUTIVE-SCALE.comment: scales dealing with quality or property of something or someone(e.g. smoothness or kindness) and are (relatively) permanent in nature. These are distinguished from ont::stage-scale types that describes scales dealing with temporary stages or states in which an entity is found (a state of being; e.g. healthiness or sleepiness).

PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-SCALE.name: PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-SCALE
PHYSICAL-PROPERTY-SCALE.comment: scales associated with properties pertaining to the attributes of physical entities or substances. Note: many properties can apply to non-physical objects.

CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-SCALE.name: CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-SCALE
CONFIGURATION-PROPERTY-SCALE.comment: scales for properties regarding the configuration, arrangement or layout of elements

APPEARANCE-SCALE.name: APPEARANCE-SCALE
APPEARANCE-SCALE.comment: scales related to surface appearance of a physical entity or object preceptible through sensory input

SOUND-SOFTNESS-SCALE.name: SOUND-SOFTNESS-SCALE
SOUND-SOFTNESS-SCALE.comment: quality of being low in volume

SENSORY-SCALE.name: SENSORY-SCALE
SENSORY-SCALE.comment: scales that deal with the quality to being perceivable through sensory input

BEHAVIORAL-SCALE.name: BEHAVIORAL-SCALE
BEHAVIORAL-SCALE.comment: scales relating to behavioral or psychological attributes that characterize an entity. Property-val counterparts in this scale include both psychological-property-val and animal-propensity-val. To be distinguished from the temporary conditions (stage-scale).

EVALUATION-SCALE.name: EVALUATION-SCALE
EVALUATION-SCALE.comment: scales relating to subjective evaluation of an entity or a situation

SIZE-SCALE.name: SIZE-SCALE
SIZE-SCALE.comment: the property of relative size or extent

UTILITY-SCALE.name: UTILITY-SCALE
UTILITY-SCALE.comment: useful function (e.g. grep - high utility, low usability)

USABILITY-SCALE.name: USABILITY-SCALE
USABILITY-SCALE.comment: ease of use (e.g. ipad - high usability, low utility)

POSITION.name: POSITION
POSITION.comment: These are stative predicates indicating the position of an object with respect to another. They also typically allow a causal variant where an agent causes this position (see ONT::CAUSE-POSITION)

RELINQUISH.name: RELINQUISH
RELINQUISH.comment: An AGENT does something that results in loss of possession or control of the AFFECTED

GIVING.name: GIVING
GIVING.comment: To relinquish control of AFFECTED AFFECTED-RESULT, typically voluntarily and possibly in exchange for something

DONATE-GIVE.name: DONATE-GIVE
DONATE-GIVE.comment: to give without expectation of any payback or return

WAIT-WATCH.name: WAIT-WATCH
WAIT-WATCH.comment: action of being attentive so as to notice something

HITTING.name: HITTING
HITTING.comment: an agent comes into contact with force with another object, typically harming the other object

COLLIDE.name: COLLIDE
COLLIDE.comment: two objects comes into contact with force with another, typically both being negatively affected - also supports the plural subject that cincludes both objects

LOCATED-MOVE-STATE.name: LOCATED-MOVE-STATE
LOCATED-MOVE-STATE.comment: a state of (passively) maintaining some object's state (e.g., position, possession)

CHANGE-INTEGRITY.name: CHANGE-INTEGRITY
CHANGE-INTEGRITY.comment: an AFFECTED undergoes a change of physical or chemical state that affects its integrity, e.g., thaw. Allows but does not require an AGENT

DEACTIVATE.name: DEACTIVATE
DEACTIVATE.comment: Stoping the running of some ongoing process or object that causes a process

CAUSE-PRODUCE-REPRODUCE.name: CAUSE-PRODUCE-REPRODUCE
CAUSE-PRODUCE-REPRODUCE.comment: an AGENT causes a new object to be created

ACTIVITY-ONGOING.name: ACTIVITY-ONGOING
ACTIVITY-ONGOING.comment: actively doing something to maintain a state (i.e., involves an agent)

CONVERSING.name: CONVERSING
CONVERSING.comment: extended interaction using communication acts, symmetric  AGENT1

EVOKE-COMFORT.name: EVOKE-COMFORT
EVOKE-COMFORT.comment: relieve of physical pain or discomfort

KNOW.name: KNOW
KNOW.comment: EXPERIENCER is certain that a situation holds

TALK.name: TALK
TALK.comment: extended communicative interaction, FORMAL is the topic of discussion

DISCUSS.name: DISCUSS
DISCUSS.comment: extended communication on a specific topic (FORMAL)

EXPLAIN.name: EXPLAIN
EXPLAIN.comment: a representative speech act that explains some situation

SAY.name: SAY
SAY.comment: A single act of verbal communication, or sequence of acts by the same agent

EXTENDED-SAY.name: EXTENDED-SAY
EXTENDED-SAY.comment: an extended series of communicative acts by an agent, following some script or structure

SCRIPTED-SAY.name: SCRIPTED-SAY
SCRIPTED-SAY.comment: an communicative acts controlled by an existing source

MANNER-SAY.name: MANNER-SAY
MANNER-SAY.comment: saying in a particular manner of speaking

NONVERBAL-SAY.name: NONVERBAL-SAY
NONVERBAL-SAY.comment: saying using a medium other that speech

BELIEF-ASCRIPTION.name: BELIEF-ASCRIPTION
BELIEF-ASCRIPTION.comment: a subclass of believe for verbs that take constructions such as 'I deem him as unsuitable'. They do not take that complements like ONT::BELIEVE verbs do

BELIEVE-SOURCE.name: BELIEVE-SOURCE
BELIEVE-SOURCE.comment: EXPERIENCER trusts or relys on some source/person/authority

NEGOTIATE.name: NEGOTIATE
NEGOTIATE.comment: extended communication with goal of reaching some agreement (RESULT)

ARGUE.name: ARGUE
ARGUE.comment: extended communication with opposing views on a topic

PLACE-IN-POSITION.name: PLACE-IN-POSITION
PLACE-IN-POSITION.comment: placing an object in a certain position: e.g., lean, sit, stand,  ...

DIG-SCOOP.name: DIG-SCOOP
DIG-SCOOP.comment: To move something incrementally, typically using a tool

PROPEL.name: PROPEL
PROPEL.comment: causing to move by a push and release activity

REMOVE-PARTS.name: REMOVE-PARTS
REMOVE-PARTS.comment: the part remaining is the good part

PARTS-REMOVED.name: PARTS-REMOVED
PARTS-REMOVED.comment: the part removed is the good part

DRY.name: DRY
DRY.comment: simply dry, neither suggests the object undergoing the drying process is intrinsically moistured or contains moisture internally (consider 'the apples dried', 'the car dried')

DEHYDRATE.name: DEHYDRATE
DEHYDRATE.comment: dehydrating process causes something that intrinsically contains moisture to be mosture-lacking (consider 'dehydrate the apples' is possible but 'dehydrate the car' is weird)

COMBINE-OBJECTS.name: COMBINE-OBJECTS
COMBINE-OBJECTS.comment: symmetric combination of objects, abstract or physical: e.g., X combines with y = y combines with x = x and y combine

MANAGING.name: MANAGING
MANAGING.comment: take responsibility over the production of a project, a program, or a production

NURTURING.name: NURTURING
NURTURING.comment: to nurture, raise, or rear humans or other animate beings; take responsibility for the growth of animate beings (compare to ont::grow)

GUIDING.name: GUIDING
GUIDING.comment: take general control over the management and direction of a program, a project, or a production

ORGANIZING.name: ORGANIZING
ORGANIZING.comment: coordinate, manage and execute a program, a project or a production

PLANNING.name: PLANNING
PLANNING.comment: make necessary preparations for a program, a project or a production

MANAGING-RESOURCES.name: MANAGING-RESOURCES
MANAGING-RESOURCES.comment: manage resources for the execution of a program, a project or a production

TAKING-CARE-OF.name: TAKING-CARE-OF
TAKING-CARE-OF.comment: take care of a problem or an issue

ARRANGING.name: ARRANGING
ARRANGING.comment: place objects in a particular physical configuration

JOINING.name: JOINING
JOINING.comment: abstract, social, or physical connection of objects such that the objects retain their original make-up/identity (whereas COMBINE-OBJECTS are not un-combinable anymore)

FIT.name: FIT
FIT.comment: join by fitting them together in a tight configuration

ATTACH.name: ATTACH
ATTACH.comment: Typically Asymmetric joining: e.g. Attach the paper to the wall =/= attach the wall to the paper!

INTERSECT.name: INTERSECT
INTERSECT.comment: two objects share a common subpart

CONNECTED.name: CONNECTED
CONNECTED.comment: two objects are touching in some way

BE-AT-LOC.name: BE-AT-LOC
BE-AT-LOC.comment: relations that indicate an postural attitude as well as a location

LEANING.name: LEANING
LEANING.comment: The state of being in a position of leaning (against something)

ORDERING.name: ORDERING
ORDERING.comment: Identify an ordering or ranking of objects along some dimention

ATTRIBUTE-IMPUTE.name: ATTRIBUTE-IMPUTE
ATTRIBUTE-IMPUTE.comment: identify a cause of an event

RELY.name: RELY
RELY.comment: EXPERIENCER relies on a certain proposition or source of information - generally allows 'on' PP

WAIT.name: WAIT
WAIT.comment: events involving waiting about, loitering, etc

SHARE.name: SHARE
SHARE.comment: two or more agents sharing something

BODY-MOVEMENT-PLACE.name: BODY-MOVEMENT-PLACE
BODY-MOVEMENT-PLACE.comment: Verbs of posture that are with respect to some place

BODY-MOVEMENT-SELF.name: BODY-MOVEMENT-SELF
BODY-MOVEMENT-SELF.comment: Verbs of posture that can be independent of any location: e.g., bow is not with respect to a location, but to sit it must be somewhere
